#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:7
msgid ""
"This page introduce the new Odoo Coding Guidelines. This guidelines aims to "
"improve the quality of the code (better readability of source, ...) but also"
" to improve Odoo Apps ! Indeed, a proper code will ease the maintenance and "
"debugging, lower the complexity and promote the reliability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:14
msgid "Module structure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:17
msgid "Directories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:18
msgid "A module is organised in a few directory :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:20
msgid "*data/* : demo and data xml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:21
msgid "*models/* : models definition"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:22
msgid "*controllers/* : contains controllers (http routes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:23
msgid "*views/* : contains the views and templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:24
msgid ""
"*static/* : contains the web assets, separated into *css/, js/, img/, lib/, "
"...*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:27
msgid "File naming"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:28
msgid ""
"For *views* declarations, split backend views from (frontend) templates in 2"
" differents files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:31
msgid ""
"For *models*, split the business logic by sets of models, in each sets "
"select a main model, this model gives its name to the set. If there is only "
"one set of module, its name is the same as the module name. For each set "
"named <main_model> the following files may be created:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:36
msgid "models/<main_model>.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:37
msgid "models/<inherited_main_model.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:38
msgid "views/<main_model>_templates.xml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:39
msgid "views/<main_model>_views.xml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:41
msgid ""
"For instance, *sale* module introduce ``sale_order`` and ``sale_order_line``"
" where ``sale_order`` is dominant. So the <main_model> files will be named "
"*models/sale_order.py* and *views/sale_order_views.py*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:47
msgid ""
"For *data*, split them by purpose : demo or data. The filename will be the "
"main_model name, suffixed by *_demo.xml* or *_data.xml*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:50
msgid "For *controller*, the only file should be named *main.py*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:52
msgid ""
"For *static files*, the name pattern is *<module_name>.ext* (i.e. : "
"static/js/im_chat.js, static/css/im_chat.css, static/xml/im_chat.xml, ...). "
"Don't link data (image, libraries) outside Odoo : don't use an url to an "
"image but copy it in our codebase instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:57
msgid "The complete tree should looks like"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:99
msgid "Filename should only use only ``[a-z0-9_]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/guidelines.rst:101
msgid "Use correct file permissions : folder 755 and file 644."
msgstr ""

